<br>
I know a bit about aggro, since i play a monk too. Cancel Magic is a nice pulling spell, because it doesnt do any &quot;damage&quot; to the mob, where damage could mean a debuff too, and thus doesnt generate a &quot;yell for help&quot;. To clarify, a mob that gets hit or &quot;damaged&quot; will &quot;yell for help&quot;, increasing the assist range of mobs around him(the radius around the mob where social mobs will join in to help).<br>
If the mob in question wasnt buffed, the spell did nothing to him. So it didnt &quot;yell&quot; because he didnt take &quot;damage&quot;, and his companions didnt even notice, since nothing happened to their friend, except those funny lights around him.<br>
Now if the mob had been buffed, and the spell removed those buffs, his friends might have noticed, depending on their initial &quot;assist range&quot;, just like they will with a resisted debuff (my guess is that they see that the mob resisted the spell, as opposed to a cancel magic when the mob has no buff to dispell, no resist needed here).<br>
If the debuff is not resisted, the mob will &quot;yell&quot;.<br>
<br>
A good example is the description of the cazic thule pull above, where the nullified mob pathed close to many others and they didnt care. What happened here was this:<br>
Mob gets nullified, but since he doesnt have buffs, nothing changes. But the mob now knows that someone tried to harm it and it puts the caster on its &quot;i know you and dont like you list&quot;. This is NOT the same list as hate! A mob can &quot;know&quot; you, but still dont hate you enough to attack(ask a monk about chain aggro..., this happens after FD, when the aggro list is wiped, but the mob still knows you are there).<br>
Well, back to the example, the mob now &quot;knows&quot; the caster, and it doesnt like him (but it doesnt &quot;hate&quot; him yet, since he didnt do anything bad to the mob), his friends dont see any damage done, and dont care(but they will also &quot;know&quot; the caster now).<br>
<br>
I hope i didnt confuse you all, but how mobs exchange their aggro/know you lists (and who knows what else...) if still unknown territory, we can only guess... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showMessageRange?topicID=62.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showPrevMessage?topicID=62.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showNextMessage?topicID=62.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=62.topic&index=24><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.threadControl?topicID=62.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=62.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=62.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Cla